Import libraries and reate connection¶

In [1]:
import psycopg2
import pandas as pd
In [2]:
# create connection with database
conn = psycopg2.connect(
    host="localhost",
    database="sneaker_park",
    user="postgres",
    password="********")

Work on the Marketing System¶

Create cursor for the

  • seller_account
  • buyer_account
  • item tables that will consist the marketing schema
In [3]:
cur_sa = conn.cursor()
cur_sa.execute("SELECT * FROM two_sided.seller_account;")
sa_list = cur_sa.fetchall()
sa_df = pd.DataFrame(sa_list, \
                    columns =['seller_id', 'first_name', 'last_name', 'email',\
                              'adress', 'zipcode']) 
print(sa_df.info())
print(sa_df.head(2))
print(sa_df.tail(2))
print(sa_df.sample(2))

Work on the Operations System¶

Create cursor for the

  • listings
  • orders
  • shipments

tables that will consist the operations schema

In [8]:
cur_li = conn.cursor()
cur_li.execute("SELECT * FROM two_sided.listings;")
li_list = cur_li.fetchall()
li_df = pd.DataFrame(li_list, \
                    columns =['listing_id','listing_price', 'listing_type', 'item_id'])
